The ''Dévastation's'' armour consisted of 183 plates of {{convert|110|mm|in|abbr=on|1}} thick wrought iron made by Creusot Rive-de-Gier, which weighed in total {{convert|297.5|t|LT|sp=us}}.<ref name=CentAnsp12/><ref name=CentAnsp14/>
In total, the five ''Dévastation''-class ironclad floating batteries cost 6,580,000 Francs (an average of 1,316,000 Francs each).<ref name=BaxterP80>Baxter, ''The introduction of the ironclad battleship'', p80. The information on costs came from a table of values of the French fleet dated 25 March 1856, which was a supporting paper 1857 budget.</ref> The ''Dévastation'' cost 1,146,489 Francs.<ref name=CentAnsp14/>
